c: 12
v: 36
t: "And two pages entered the prison with him. One of them said, \"Surely I (do) see myself (in a dream) that I was pressing wine. \"And the other said, \"Surely I (do) see myself (in a dream) that I was carrying above my head bread that birds were eating of. Fully inform us of its interpretation; surely we see you (are) (one) of the fair-doers"